ol.li:
 Let \(A = \left(
\begin{array}{cc}
 2 & 3 \\
 1 & 4 \\
\end{array}
\right)\) and \(B =\left(
\begin{array}{cc}
 3 & -3 \\
 2 & 1 \\
\end{array}
\right)\). Verify that \((A B)^{-1}= B^{-1}A^{-1}\) .

exercise.statement:
 Let Let \(A =\left(
\begin{array}{cc}
 a & b \\
 c & d \\
\end{array}
\right)\). Derive the formula for \(A^{-1}\).

 Prove by induction that for \(n \geq 1\), \(\left(
\begin{array}{cc}
 a & 0 \\
 0 & b \\
\end{array}
\right)^n= \left(
\begin{array}{cc}
 a^n & 0 \\
 0 & b^n \\
\end{array}
\right)\).

